<text id="A7133T">
<front id="d2">
<div1 type="summary" id="d3">
<p>Scott informs Smith about the teachers' dire need for proper "beding." </p> 
</div1> 
 
</front> 

<body id="d4">
<div1 type="letter" id="d5">
<head>
<name type="recipient">Mr Smith</name> 
<name type="place">Staunton Va</name> 
</head>

<opener>
<dateline>
    <date value="1868-12-26">Dec 26th/68</date> 
</dateline> 
<salute></salute> 
</opener> 

<p>I am much troubled about beding for the lady who came down without it.</p>
	<p>If you send another teacher instead of, or in adition to this one (one of which I hope you will do for I am almost discouraged) please have her bring some beding.</p>
	<p>I dont want to buy anything here or any more than necessary</p>

<p>1 Blanket in office<lb/>
2 Blanket<lb/>
2 Quilts<lb/>
1 <unclear>Bedside</unclear><lb/>
1 <del rend="none" hand="h1"></del><lb/>
1 Pillow<lb/></p>

<closer>
<salute>Very Respectfully</salute> 
<signed>John Scott</signed> 

</closer> 
</div1> 
</body> 
</text> 
